<br>
On malosini/malosi, difference between those spells are how much they debuff (malosi is 59 at start), the level of the spell, cast time, mana, recast time and duration. Notice those have nothing to do with resists. Your resist come slower cause you take longer to cast and recast, but you use less mana and get same ratio of resist as me with malosini. It IS frustrating to see it resisted that much. But it's also very powerful, pretty much second best debuff line in game imho. Also if you lower resist on malosi thinking it's not gonna affect those with malosini, yes it will, cause i would mem both and try malosi first, and that's wrong hehe. My opinion is this spell line is fine. You might differ and you're welcome express it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Guess lvl 54 spell don't do jack cept save bag space and cost money, told ya I didn't have a clue about it, never casted once, got transon's first. Zipping it on that one, you have my vote. ;P<br>
<br>
For proc'in weapon, we agree we should get it, but not on how much dmg, I only mentioned that as a player I thought 250 proc like you first suggested was too high. Talking for epic here but if he dual weild 250dd proc weapons, he's gonna be tearing up some serious ass. As for making pet only able to use 1 of those weapon, there's 2 solution. Making pets aware that something is lore and destroy when multiple lore item present (depending on how much they split pet from being npc (remember line is thin, pets ARE npc), this could be hard to code). Second solution is introduce a new status &quot;pet weapon&quot; and code the validation in. Takes a bit more CPU juice, but doable. But then why not make weapon 125 damage proc and let everything else as is? That's my point, 50-75 procs damage weapons would be very cool with me, especialy if they were lure saves procs. Maybe put ancient summon sword of own at 100 dmg, but going above that might be too strong (remember I'm hoping for lure type procs P).<br>
<br>
