Like you mentioned the resists on that spell line are pretty high. The advantage of malosini are mainly it's faster cast time and the fact that you can chain cast it. Getting malosi/malosini to stick on a mob is a really huge advantage in most situations. While it's frustrating at 51 to get high resist and long wait between recast, it's still a pretty nice spell when you go against something big that could be slowed. And at 58 we get an upgrade and then you chain cast it through resists until it stick, then usualy a few sec later a shaman tells the guild/raid/group Target slowed. Sometimes you get mobs that can only be hit with malo/mala, then you deal with that hehe. Repeating myself but I that spell line is fine as is . It is resisted a lot, but it's minimal aggro and -60 to all but desease helps a lot of people in said guild/raid/group. It's also very satisfying to get it in after 2-3 resists when there's a few mage casting it on &lt;insert random nicely tuned resist huge mob&gt;. The entire malo line rocks, resisted a lot but for a reason hehe.<br>
