Mesana </a> ( Dark Elf ) <a href="http://www.remedy.fr.st" > Remedy </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#333333>(7/24/02 7:06:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=272.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thoughts for Rich on additional changes</span><hr size=1> I agree with most of what people have said already, especially the argument about leaving room for evocation-based mages (I am one at level 50).  But here is my personal priority list:<br>
<br>
1.  Fix haste cap for pets.  Doesn't directly affect me at my level, but it's rather stupid to have higher-lvl spells that don't do much.  No reason to have a cap.<br>
<br>
2.  Make Frenzied Burnout better.  Again, not affecting me for a while, but since every other caster has a &quot;killer AA&quot; that they have, mages should too.  And by killer, i mean both in desire to have it, and will literally kill many non-boss mobs, and be of REAL help on raids.  The suggestion for this that I like most is making your pet hit for extreme damage, very fast, with a lot of health, for a duration governed by the amount of mana you have at casting, and drains ALL of it.  And pet explodes with a big bang at the end of it.  Manaburn for mages should be Frenzied Burnout.  Have it do comparable damage to manaburn.  And make sure the pet has enough health to survive the agro it will get with it's hits!<br>
<br>
3.  Make us the kings of damage shields.  We always were pre-50, but continue it by increasing our post-50 offerings.  Not by much, since we weren't much over before, but nonetheless, better.<br>
<br>
4.  Make us nuke better than Druids.  Yes it's class envy.  But they shouldn't even APPROACH mages or wizards.  We shouldn't approach wizards either, but having ANY non-ancient spell that is better than mages is ludicrus (sp?).<br>
<br>
5.  Resist rate on the malise line.  The whole reason of this line is to debuff so our nukes CAN hit, but if the debuff can't hit, then what's the point?<br>
<br>
6.  Look at pets in the 24-38 range.  They really lack compared to anything else in this twink-heavy world.  They start coming back into power 39-50.  The lower-level mages need to be seen as more useful to a group.<br>
<br>
7.  Look at pets 50+.  The damage output of them has been improved for the GVoc line (except air, fix that), but the Voc aren't significantly harder-hitting than the 49s.  Not to mention their large level difference with the mobs we are fighting.  This is a problem through a mage's whole career really.  The large level difference makes what would SEEM to be like a good damage-output pet (via max hit), but hardly ever hits for that, so therefore not-so-hot.  Pets shouldn't completely blow everything away, but they need looking at how to increase the amount that they hit.<br>
<br>
These are what concern me.  I probably missed a lot, but whatever I did I'm sure that others covered.  The AA needs serious looking at as well to see what's USEFUL, but others have covered that topic far better than I.<br>
<br>
/rant on<br>
The basic idea here is that mages need to be seen as bringing something NEEDED to a group.  Wizards and mages are sometimes seen as &quot;filler&quot; to an exp group.  My brother (a 49 chanter) has even commented to me in his Dreadland days, that to him, the best group is a Shadowknight (best agro-keeping tank), Ranger (sow, snare), Monk, Rogue (can ditch monk for two rogues), cleric, and enchanter (crack cleric, and mez power).  In that environment he's right.  High-dmg output, low downtime, adds handled.  A mage isn't a substitue for a monk or a rogue for damage output, and what we offer isn't as useful.  Somebody on this board said it before:  Mages should be the rogues of casters.  High-dmg output, few defensive skills, since VI doesn't seem to want to give us anything to defend ourselves with (gate doesn't count).  We need to be seen as useful somehow.<br>
/rant off<br>
<br>
Anyways, keep the changes coming.  For better or for worse, at least you're trying to help us out.<br>
 <p>Eriol Telcontar - Dragons Revolt<BR>
Magician of the 50th Summoning<BR>
