<td align="center"><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=293427">My Magelo Profile</a></td></tr>
</table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utipareth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tipareth</A> at: 7/30/02 4:41:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udurash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Durash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(7/31/02 7:03:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=272.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thoughts for Rich on additional changes</span><hr size=1> Okay, I’m inspired to write this, even after three years of dealing with the useless predecessors of Rich.  I’ve seen a few changes, and I’m happy that we’re finally getting some notice – Rich, do you play a magician?  If you don’t, you actually give the impression that you’ve looked into this with some level of serious intent.  Thank you for that.<br>
<br>
Prior representatives have claimed “Yes, we have people here who play magicians,” but I am dead-set convinced that they have either been (a) Lying through their teeth, or (b) ignoring the mythical players they refer to.  <br>
<br>
With that said, here’s my thinking on stuff.<br>
<br>
Pet Haste.  Fix it.  Why are there spells for 65% haste if pet can’t get past 60%?  /boggle.  I don’t understand why there’s even a cap.  Please elaborate.<br>
<br>
Include the pets that were “left out” of the recent patch in the next one.  Air and MS lines, specifically.<br>
<br>
What ever happened to the idea of summoning procing weapons that was mentioned two years ago when our bugged Sword of Runes was fixed?  There was talk of introducing a line of fire, cold, magic, etc. based weapons.  They don’t have to be major procs, it would just be nice to see a set of them at 29th to match the SoR.  Nothing higher than the 38pts that SoR does, in fact I’d be happy seeing some 25s there.  I’m not sure what planet the 250pt suggestion came from, but that’s plain nuts.  VI has stated categorically they don’t want a sea of phantom weapons creeping around, and if a 250pt proccer started showing up in magician summons, you’d see about a hundred werewolf forms holding these in every zone you travelled.  86 that idea.<br>
<br>
Bravo on focus item summons.  Thank you.  <br>
<br>
Some other suggestions for summons:  Summon Boots of Travel (maybe equivalent to Run2, or Run3, one or two charges of effect) as a mid-50s.  Summon Bow of Whateveryouwanttocallit (minor usefulness, but would round out the collection).  Summon Lava Diamond (someone else mentioned this earlier, I like it).  I’ll think of others.<br>
<br>
TPP is enough mana regen for us.  That’s not our bag.  I wouldn’t mind seeing it upped to 6pts, that would seem to follow more closely with druid and cleric spells (what I’m saying here is I don’t understand the rationale behind ours being 3pts while theirs are 6pts – I’d be happier if someone tried to explain this to me).<br>
<br>
Quillmane.  Remove him and replace with a god-level mob indifferent to everyone.  Make him BIGNUTS tough, so it requires at least 30 lvl 57+ to get him.  I’m sick of watching Druid farmers bending magicians over a barrel.  It’s not as if this would change the quantity of cloaks in the game, it would simply let us feel less raped when we need one.<br>
<br>
I see no need for evocation bonuses on our class – those who wished to become evokers got what they wanted – there’s a decent spell for that, and they’ve got a damage machine pet to go with it.  They’ll never add up to wizards on nukes – and should never come close.  The pet causes more damage than the wizard ever will, for a fixed amount of mana.  300-500 mana and you’ve got a chunk of damage that might just last you all day long.  That should be enough.  I was a little irked that Druids get a larger nuke, but when it comes down to brass tacks, Gonad and my nukes can put Druids to shame on the DPS scale.  And I do mean shame.  As in “Stand over there, heal me when I need it, and watch what the BOSS can do.”<br>
<br>
I see no need to change existing Damage Shields, but would it be possible to get a message saying “So-and-so’s Cadeau of Flame has worn off”?  Probably not, but would be nice.<br>
<br>
Debuffs are fine.  Resist rates are fine.  I understand where you’re coming from, Imaginos9, but you’re going to have to trust us on this one, get a few more levels and grow your guild some.  Malosi is a pulling spell, not a raiding one.  Malosini is the chain-casting ROCK.  When your crowd goes to HoT, you’ll start using it for real – someone else lands Mala/Malo, someone tash’s, you chain-cast Malosini and as soon as you land it, not only will the shaman’s slow stick, but when the raid leader calls “NUKE”, that things hps will evaporate.  <br>
<br>
Forget bandages.  Bandages are for giving to monks, and *possibly* for use solo to recover to 50% WHILE you have TPP or another armor form ticking on you.  Bandages are a totally worthless discussion to be having relative to our class, guys.  <br>
<br>
I don’t think I’ve realistically used any of the Ward Summoned line of spells since I was leveling in LavaStorm three years ago.  Care to guess why that is?  Here’s why:  my regular nukes are as effective, generally faster casting, and when I run into a non-summoned critter, they work.  Why would I use a summoned-specific nuke when the regular one works almost exactly the same?  Even if this line was better ratio or faster, or whatever, there aren’t really a lot of opportunities to use it.  Youngling elementals, Shadowed Men, BW Wasps, and Rumblecrush’s buddies.  Are there spots I’m missing here?<br>
<br>
AA stuff:<br>
<br>
FB – change it.  Everyone is asking for something like an MB/LB and also I see requests for Dire Charm style ability.  I’ve *also* seen requests that we be given the choice of evoc v. conjuration.  I personally see no need for MB/LB style nukage on our class.  Rather, I see us working with the pet – and I would like to see the pet work as well as a DC mob.  Therefore, I suggest FB be a major buff, not a “ticking time-bomb of fury.”  <br>
<br>
1 - Make FB a permanent effect, keep the 144min timer on it.  Pet gets bumped to mob-style output (assuming he’s not already there), and stays there, much as if an enchanter had DC’d a mob.  Pet has no explosive property AT ALL.  <br>
<br>
If you insist on introducing an MB-style effect, here:<br>
<br>
2 – Add a new AA on par (difficulty in acquiring) with FB.  “Elemental Instability” – this makes the pet the bomb that current FB was supposed to.  Same 144min timer restriction.  Pet explodes upon reaching AE range with the mob.  When pet dies, it explodes for double his *current* hps as a PBAE, 30 seconds from putting the effect on him.  So if he’s been doing melee damage and getting output that way, and the mob has mashed him down to zero (or he takes a 1200pt AE on the way in), he explodes for less-than-optimal.  If the caster sent him in full and told him to /get lost, he’ll blow for full damage.  I’d like to see possible crits on this, but I can’t really imagine a realistic justification.  This effect should NOT be allowed to stack with ANY other spell or effect (i.e., no Aego prior to rushing in), and both FB and EI would be tied to same timer – so choose ONE to work with at any given moment.<br>
<br>
Elemental Forms...these have been discussed ad nauseam in other threads.  I don’t know what to say to this, other than for my own choice I’ll be picking either Water or Water unless/until something changes.  Doesn’t seem enough benefit to the others, and I haven’t really researched them heavily enough to make statements yet.<br>
<br>
Get rid of First Aid.  That’s about on par with Bristlebane’s Bundle, and I’m not spending a kajillion xps on it.  I can’t imagine a fantasy role-playing justification for this, either.  You could improve the Mend Companion line…that would be a nice replacement for this.<br>
<br>
Turn Summoned?  Please tell me, where would I use this effectively other than in Umbral Plains when we’re about to wipe because someone brought too many of Rumblecrush’s assistants?  Dump this, please, unless you’re planning on making a LOT more summoned mobs in the high-end game on which this effect would stick.<br>
<br>
Improved Reclaim Energy?  I’ve got half a dozen things that reclaim energy already.  Enough with this.  If you want to give us mana regen ability, get serious about it and stop with this bullcrap.  Every time I see an item with this on it, I keep thinking of that scene in Spinal Tap where the guy continues to insist “Mine goes to eleven.”  I want to shake someone’s head to see if I can hear the marbles clattering around in there.  What, exactly, is the point of all this fecal matter?<br>
<br>
Lose Mass Group Buff.  What use do we have for this?  As a magician, I would never spend time learning this, since it has no useful outcome.  Unless you’re going to let us throw Transon’s Protection on everyone in range.<br>
<br>
Elemental Pact…Okay, this is mildly cool.  I’m epic’d, so it means pretty much nothing to me, but for a lot of folks this will help.  Thank you.  Might be nice if this also affected the material requirement for Banishment (since Banishment also removes the xp and looting possibilities, I’d say it costs enough as is).<br>
<br>
Arch had a neat idea up there with his “Finale” pet idea.  Interesting.  Probably would be EXTREMELY rare to have six mages with that talent even online at the same time, but cool idea anyhow.<br>
<br>
Now, regarding some of the other posts I’ve read here…<br>
<br>
Uaellaen, was your point #1 a joke?  That’s got to be the worst accounting of a magician that I’ve ever heard.  If that’s really how you play, thank god you’re not on my server, magicians would have the worst rep around.  Everyone has a higher damage output than YOU, maybe, but you would be best advised to speak for yourself.  How lame can you be?  I solo regularly in Akheva Ruins, The Grey, Scarlet Desert, yadda yadda, and I don’t even 2box with a cleric.  What’s your malfunction?<br>
<br>
I see a few people saying they want to be NEEDED in a group.  What a load of horseshit.  I’m a DPS machine, and I’m not incredibly uber-equipped.  Even without epic, I unload a TON of damage.  As long as I manage agro properly, I’m fine.  People who know me, know that.  People who don’t know me, are pleasantly surprised when they watch me pick off adds and perform crowd control.  I regularly hear “Holy crap, look at that pet go!”  We as a class are already NEEDED in a group.  I’m guessing that most of the folks who don’t see this are either (1) crappy players, or (2) don’t know how to find people to group with.  Switching classes or uber-ifying magicians won’t help you.  Quit now or get over your lack of talent.<br>
<br>
You guys are so upset about warriors/rogues/monks having higher DPS…big freaking deal.  Warrior needs a cleric.  Rogue needs a taunter.  Monk is probably the closest thing to a soloer among those three, and that one is almost as fragile as I am.  We’ve got remote control tankage guys, make the best of it.  We can do things these classes simply cannot.  Stop your bitching about how so-and-so has better armor than me and can still do more damage.  Guess what?  He’s gonna take a lot more too, and he doesn’t have the option of gating away, or summoning a new 3k of hit points, when things go wrong.<br>
<br>
Try a pet group sometime, you guys.  That rivals AE any day of the week.  What a freaking load of whining.<br>
<br>
<br>
Later - <br>
<br>
  Big D <p>Durash L'Cyphier
the Faerless

Evening Reign
Druzzil Ro

